item.title: Border closures hurt share market
item.description: The Australian stock market closed lower on Monday as state border closures with Victoria sparked fear of a second wave that could damage the country’s economic rebound.

item.title: Doc guilty of assaulting sleeping patients
item.description: A Sydney doctor has been found guilty of indecently assaulting female patients as they slept, including touching their bodies, masturbating next to them and placing his penis in a girl’s hand.

item.title: How Melbourne outbreak affects us all
item.description: Health officials warn that Victoria’s COVID-19 outbreak remains a national issue, with 140 Australians testing positive in the past 24 hours.

item.title: Two dead in state’s worst virus day
item.description: Two Victorians have died from coronavirus on the same day the state recorded its highest daily number of new cases since the pandemic started.

item.title: Man fighting for life after M1 crash
item.description: A man is fighting for life after he was hit by a truck on one of Australia’s busiest motorways.

item.title: Man fleeing virus tower bites cop
item.description: A man has been arrested after he allegedly bit a police offer while trying to leave the locked-down public housing flats in Melbourne’s north.

item.title: Car rolls in Sydney Harbour Tunnel
item.description: Traffic came to a brief standstill on Monday afternoon after a man, aged in his 40s, rolled his Toyota Yaris in the Sydney Harbour Tunnel.

item.title: Pokie tax jackpot for pubs, clubs
item.description: Queensland pubs and clubs have been given a $50 million break in gaming taxes.

item.title: Aussies raid $18b from their savings
item.description: More than $18 billion has been sapped from the country’s superannuation sector, as millions of Australians claim financial hardship due to COVID-19.

item.title: Cabin crew replace hotel guards
item.description: Qantas and Jetstar airline staff will be brought in to work in Melbourne’s quarantine hotels.
